The '''Nalle triplets''',<ref name="CSWE" /> or the '''Nalle sisters''', comprised of [[Mya Nalle]], [[Yma Nalle]] and [[Lela Nalle Mayn]],<ref name="Insider" /> a trio of identical<ref name="CSWE" /> [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="Insider" /> [[Gender/Legends|female]] sisters who lived on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="CSWE" /> The only [[Marriage/Legends|married]] triplet, Lela, was an [[Architect/Legends|architect]] and [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] of the planet [[Commenor/Legends|Commenor]]. She came to the [[University of Coruscant/Legends|University of Coruscant]] to study architecture.<ref name="Insider" /> The triplets were subtly effective<ref name="db" /> [[Spy/Legends|spies]] for corrupt [[Mayor/Legends|Mayor]] [[Acros-Krik]],<ref name="DB2">{{DB|character|lelamayn|Mayn, Lela Nalle}}</ref> who offered them as guides to targets he wanted monitored. They reported to the mayor any useful information their guests foolishly divulged.<ref name="db2">{{DB|character|acros_krik|Acros-Krik}}</ref>

The triplets, who were considered attractive,<ref name="db">{{DB|character|acros_krik|Acros-Krik}}</ref> commonly went to the [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] halls and [[Casino/Legends|casinos]] in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of Coruscant. They used their femininity to distract other gamblers while stealing their [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]].<ref name="CSWE" /> Mayn unfortunately found herself studying the architecture of establishments like the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="Insider" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and gambling hall in the Uscru District.<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Mya Nalle, Yma Nalle and Lela Mayn, seen in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']], were all portrayed by an uncredited [[Amy Allen]]. All of the triplets' names are anagrams of her name.

The shot in which Mya and Yma Nalle appear was completed after principal photography using a limited number of actors and costumes, with some being duplicated to better populate the shot. The idea of the Nalle triplets was used to explain why two such similar-looking women appeared in one shot, with Lela Mayn later being confirmed as the third Nalle sister.

